<title>UK: Halifax underlying profit up six percent.</title>
<headline>Halifax underlying profit up six percent.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-08-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months to June 1996</p>
<p>			  (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Pretax			 649		  vs 656</p>
<p> Excep admin charges	88.2		 vs 7.7</p>
<p> Total debt provision     54		   vs 57.0</p>
<p> Tax			    223.1		vs 225.7</p>
<p>NOTE - The building society group reported that gross mortgage lending for the period was 4.8 billion stg, with net mortgage lending of 585 million. It also stated that underlying profit growth for the first six months of 1996 was six percent ahead, stripping out exceptionals.</p>
</text>
